The paper deals with optimization problems related to multi-user interference channels, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of beamforming and single-user detection techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents theoretical results on the achievable rate region, which may be of interest to researchers in the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
